				 Preferential shares for Essar Oil promoters
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, Nov. 23: Essar Oil will seek shareholders approval for a preferential allotment of shares or other equity-linked instruments of up to $2 billion to Essar Energy Holdings, the Mauritius-based parent company.																								The company said it might allot a part of the issue to promoters or associates of the holding company through any financial instrument which would be convertible into equity shares of face value Rs 10.																								The shareholders will vote on the proposal at an extraordinary general meeting on December 18.																								The final structure of the preferential allotment will be decided at the meeting where Naresh Kumar Nayyar will be formally appointed as the companys managing director.																								The preferential offer will be issued outside India with or without a premium. 																								Last week, Essar Oil announced plans to invest about $6 billion to increase the capacity at its Vadinar refinery from 10.5 million tonnes to 34 million tonnes per annum.																								The companys board had then announced plans to issue global depository shares worth about $2 billion to the promoters of the company or the group on a preferential basis. 
